section.t:
A simplified operation scenario of offloading content, such as video stream, from a congested or costly Internet connection to a white space service provided by an AP consists of the following steps: The AP contacts the database to determine channels it can use.
The portable device connects to a paid Internet service and selects a video for streaming.
The portable device determines if it can offload to a white space access point: If the portable device knows its location, it asks the database (using the paid service) for available white-space spectrum;
listens for and connects to the AP over the permitted white-space spectrum.
If the portable device does not have GPS or other means to determine its position, it uses non-white-space spectrum to listen for and connect to the AP;
asks the AP to query the database for permitted white-space spectrum on its behalf;
uses the permitted white-space spectrum to connect to the AP.
The portable device accesses the Internet through the AP to stream the selected video.
